What is Primary key important points and rules


A Primary Key (PK) uniquely identifies each row in a table.
 Think of it as the table’s identity column.

1.Uniqueness (Mandatory) :: No duplicate values allowed

2.NOT NULL (Mandatory)   :: Cannot contain NULL

3. Only one Primary key per table :: But it can be composite (multiple columns)

4.Automatically Indexed
DB creates a unique index for fast lookup
👉 Improves performance of searches & joins

5.Stable (Should not change)
Avoid updating PK values frequently
👉 Can break relationships with other tables

6.Used for Relationships (Foreign Key)












